Get a first look at Photos for Mac, Apple's replacement for iPhoto and ApertureÃ¢â‚¬â€coming soon to Mac OS X. In this course, staff author Garrick Chow outlines the key features of the public beta version of Photos for Mac, including its streamlined interface design, photo editing tools, and connection to iCloud, which offers almost instant library syncing between Mac OS X and iOS devices. The course also describes how to get and install the latest Yosemite public beta and details some considerations for converting iPhoto and Aperture libraries.
